Timer sync hardening log
=======================

Objective
- Audit and harden game clock behavior for refresh/reconnect and idle timeout scenarios.

Findings from audit
- Clock deduction originally happened only on move events; refresh/reconnect could show stale server time until next move.
- If a player moved after their own clock already expired (while idle), server still accepted move and only flagged timeout in mixed paths.
- Frontend had no explicit periodic authoritative sync request; relied mostly on local countdown + move broadcasts.

Changes made

1) Added `djangoChess/main/timer_sync.py`
- New `sync_game_clock(game, now=None)` centralizes server-authoritative clock deduction.
- Rules enforced:
  - No deduction before game start (`last_move_timestamp` is null).
  - Deduct only active side by reading FEN turn token.
  - Clamp to zero, set winner on timeout, clear draw offer on timeout.

2) Updated `djangoChess/main/consumers.py`
- On websocket connect, sends immediate authoritative `state_sync` payload.
- Added message type `sync_state` so client can request periodic state reconciliation.
- Added DB path `sync_and_get_game_state()` that applies `sync_game_clock()` and persists updates.
- Move handling now uses `update_game_data()` result object:
  - If timeout is detected before applying the incoming move, move is rejected and `game_over` timeout is broadcast.
  - Otherwise move applies and broadcast includes authoritative times/outcome.
- `state_sync` now includes `game_started` derived from `last_move_timestamp`.

3) Updated `djangoChess/main/templates/main/board2.html`
- On websocket open: immediately requests `sync_state`.
- Added periodic `sync_state` request every 2s while game active.
- Unified handling for `move` and `state_sync` updates to keep board + clocks authoritative.
- `gameStarted` now sourced from server when provided, preventing pre-start countdown drift.
- Avoided duplicate game-over handling path introduced during patching.

4) Added `djangoChess/main/test_timer_sync.py`
- `test_sync_game_clock_no_drain_before_first_move`
- `test_sync_game_clock_deducts_active_side_and_times_out`
- `test_sync_game_clock_uses_black_clock_when_black_to_move`
- These lock key scenarios for start-state, active-side deduction, and timeout resolution.

Validation
- Full test suite run after timer changes: PASS.
- Result: 28 passed, 0 failed.

Scenario coverage summary
- Refresh/reconnect: client requests server state on connect and every 2s.
- Idle timeout without move: timeout finalized on sync path.
- Move-after-time-expired race: server rejects move and emits timeout game-over.
- Pre-start lobby/waiting opponent: no time drains until first move timestamp exists.

