Django message UX fix log
=========================

Problem observed
- Flash messages created via Django `messages` were not consistently visible on immediate redirect targets (especially lobby/game pages), causing perceived delay until user navigated elsewhere.

Root cause
- Message rendering was duplicated inconsistently across templates.
- Critical redirect targets (`lobby.html`, `board2.html`) lacked a standard flash message render block.

Changes made

1) Added reusable message partial
- New file: `main/templates/main/partials/flash_messages.html`
- Handles standard message levels (`error`, `warning`, `success`, default info) with consistent styling.

2) Wired message partial into key immediate-redirect pages
- `main/templates/main/lobby.html`: include flash messages near top of container.
- `main/templates/main/board2.html`: include flash messages near top of game container.

3) Unified existing pages to use same component
- `main/templates/main/create_game.html`
- `main/templates/main/set_address.html`
